title: Eagles links: Chip Kelly to North Texas State? latest on Kiko Alonso, Nelson ... - NJ.com
text:
PHILADELPHIA -- Even as the Eagles prepare for Monday night's showdown with the Giants that could determine the early lead in the NFC East race , head coach Chip Kelly was forced to address speculation that he'd be heading back to college . 
"No," Kelly said when asked if either the University of Southern California or South Carolina had inquired about luring him away from the NFL. "North Texas State. [joking] The Armadillos or whatever." 
The Texas State Fightin' Armadillos were the fictional college football program from the 1991 movie 'Necessary Roughness.' 
Clearly, Kelly had given the recent speculation plenty of credence. 
The third-year NFL head coach tried his best to put the rumors to bed, saying that he hoped to one day win enough games and be as successful as Giants head coach Tom Coughlin in order to finally shed the label as a 'college coach.'
